## Current Issues & Recommendations

### 1. Missing Body Parsing Middleware
The app has no `express.json()` or `express.urlencoded()` middleware. Any future POST/PUT routes would silently receive unparsed bodies.

### 2. No Input Validation
There's no validation on query parameters or route params. For example, if you add `/users/:id`, an unsanitized value could be passed downstream unsafely.

### 3. No Rate Limiting
The app is open to abuse without any request throttling.

### 4. No Global Error Handler
Unhandled errors in route handlers will crash or leak stack traces to the client.

### 5. No Security Headers
Without `helmet`, the app exposes default headers that reveal server details and miss important browser-security protections.

### 6. Hardcoded Port
`3000` is hardcoded rather than read from the environment.

---

## Suggested Improved Version

```js
const express = require('express');
const helmet = require('helmet');
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');

const app = express();
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;

// ─── Security Headers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
app.use(helmet());

// ─── Body Parsing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));        // Prevents large payload attacks
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false, limit: '10kb' }));

// ─── Rate Limiting ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 100,                  // Limit each IP to 100 requests per window
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
  message: { error: 'Too many requests, please try again later.' },
});
app.use(limiter);

// ─── Routes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
app.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
});

app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  // Input validation example: sanitize query params if added later
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    { id: 2, name: 'Bob', email: 'bob@example.com' },
  ]);
});

// ─── 404 Handler ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
app.use((req, res) => {
  res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
});

// ─── Global Error Handler ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// eslint-disable-next-line no-unused-vars
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);  // Log internally — never expose stack to client
  const status = err.status || err.statusCode || 500;
  const message = status < 500 ? err.message : 'Internal server error';
  res.status(status).json({ error: message });
});

// ─── Start Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
if (require.main === module) {
  app.listen(PORT, () => {
    console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
  });
}

module.exports = app;
```

